My brother called to inform them and they were not helpful and instead defensive saying we couldn’t “prove anything”. This was the only meal my brother and I shared this whole weekend. They were unwilling to do anything about it. Additionally, for a steakhouse, they were ill-prepared and out of three popular types of cuts (the whole reason we went). My brother asked for the steak he ordered to be cooked medium and it came out very, very rare. The inside was cold. I will never recommend this place and will absolutely never go back again. I chose the Grillroom for dining because of the positive reviews and the proximity to the CIBC theater. I must say that I am extremely disappointed. First things first: You’ve got to try the seafood gumbo. The roux is dark and gives the gumbo an ideal smooth texture as it thickens, and adds a wonderfully nutty aroma. The seafood stock is earthy and melded into the roux very well. The peppers add just a l’il kick. For our visit this evening, our party of three was seated in a booth immediately at 9PM, and we ordered the salmon entree, and a couple filet mignon entrees (an entire roasted garlic clove accompanied each steak). Sides were string beans, and brussel sprouts with crispy smoked bacon bits. The food arrived without much delay, piping hot and full of flavors. (I photographed a few shots here). Wine and cocktails were refreshing. Server was attentive to our requests. Prices here aren’t cheap, but competitive for the neighborhood. Portions are generous, so we passed up dessert. Check out the Grillroom Chophouse — you won’t be disappointed.

I read the reviews online and made my reservation before seeing Hamilton. My reservation was complete with my remarks we were seeing Hamilton. The restaurant atmosphere was lovely and the food was divine. Our reservation was for 5:45 and we were promptly seated on time. I expected to be in there easily an hour. I thought we'd have enough time to get outside and take a few pictures before we got in line for the show. I read this elsewhere and I have to agree, it was a little too slow. The waiter was fantastic and kind but I didn't think our dessert would ever get to us. Of course you want to be seated in the theater in plenty of time to freshen up, use the restroom, whatever... before you get your seats. Dessert finally arrived at 7:00 p.m. and we had to eat fast even though the theater was across the street so we could get in line and get settled. We didn't get into our seats until 7:20. If the service was't quite so slow, I would easily give 5 stars and two thumbs up but it just shouldn't take 20 min. to get dessert and then not have the time to enjoy it. I would definitely go back but arrange my time better so I don't stress.
